name: NY AG James
tweet: I am deeply disturbed by the situation unfolding in Monsey, New York tonight.   There is zero tolerance for acts of hate of any kind and we will continue to monitor this horrific situation.    I stand with the Jewish community tonight and every night.

name: NY AG James
tweet: The Trump Admin’s @EPA is seeking to reverse regulations that are critical to protecting the health of our water.   Repealing the Clean Water Act ignores science and will only put our nation’s waters and our communities in harm’s way.   I’m suing.    https://t.co/SgrWXMlrp9

name: NY AG James
tweet: The #ACA’s contraceptive mandate has helped women maintain autonomy over their own reproductive choices, and we won't go backwards and let the federal government undo all the progress that's been made.  We submitted a brief to defend women's full & equal access to birth control.

name: NY AG James
tweet: Happy #Kwanzaa to all who celebrate. Tonight, we begin this weeklong holiday that celebrates and honors the beautiful culture & traditions of African Americans, heritage that has enriched every aspect of our country. May your celebration be filled with community and love.

name: NY AG James
tweet: The sharp increase in anti-Semitic hate crimes is alarming, especially during Hanukkah. No one should be afraid to walk the streets of New York based on their religious identity.   We are better than this.    https://t.co/RcOUvurb6M

name: NY AG James
tweet: A very Merry Christmas to everyone celebrating today!  May you have a joyous day with your family and all of those you love.

name: NY AG James
tweet: From preserving our environment, to standing up for consumers, to safeguarding our civil rights and beyond, we were busy in 2019.  See our annual report below for highlights of our key actions this year.   https://t.co/xIo77MgBW3

name: NY AG James
tweet: Happy #Hanukkah to all who begin celebrating tonight.   May these eight days be filled with light and happiness as you spend time with your family, friends, and loved ones.   Chag Sameach!

name: NY AG James
tweet: We found @Starbucks illegally required their employees to find a substitute when using sick leave & if they couldn't, they faced discipline, including termination.  This is a blatant violation of our laws, and @NYCMayor and I held them accountable.   https://t.co/Bx9r4SLwhW

name: NY AG James
tweet: The @EPA is trying to ignore science and strip our nation's waters of basic protections.  I'm leading a multistate lawsuit to fight against these rollbacks because access to clean water is a fundamental right for New Yorkers and all Americans.

name: NY AG James
tweet: The Trump Admin has issued a rule that will bar people, many of whom are fleeing violence & persecution, from seeking asylum in the US and send them to third countries instead.   This rule is antithetical to our nation’s values, and I’m opposing it.

name: NY AG James
tweet: Our state judicial system cannot properly function with the interference of ICE in our courthouses.  Today's ruling ensures we will get our day in court to fight for justice and public safety for all New Yorkers.  https://t.co/1Yn6iVdNRL

name: NY AG James
tweet: We won't allow anyone to get away with denying hard-working New Yorkers their wages or cheat New York by fraudulently obtaining tax breaks.   I'm proud to have helped recover and deliver the payment these workers should have received long ago.

name: NY AG James
tweet: Following our settlement, we secured over $400K in recovered wages for building service workers who were cheated out of their hard-earned money.  I'd like to thank @NYCComptroller & @kyle32bj for their partnership in ensuring the workers of New York get the pay they deserve.  https://t.co/l9GpR2uEqc

name: NY AG James
tweet: Thanks to everyone who joined @bradhoylman and me tonight @GC_CUNY for our town hall to discuss issues impacting New Yorkers.  Your engagement is critical to our ability to best serve the people of New York.  https://t.co/bn7FvnKACA

name: NY AG James
tweet: We're opposing a @forestservice rule that would strip Alaska's Tongass National Forest from protections against road construction & timber harvesting.  The rule will endanger wildlife & undermine state efforts to mitigate the impacts on climate change.   We won't stand for it.

name: NY AG James
tweet: The Worst Landlords List is a critical tool to expose bad landlords & hold them accountable for the horrible conditions they force New Yorkers to live in.   Thanks to @NYCPA for continuing the legacy of this list & our commitment to protecting tenants.  https://t.co/vylKFCEdp3

tweet: We will continue to do everything in our power to protect survivors and ensure hospitals abide by this crucial law.   If you’ve been wrongly billed for these tests, please know that my office is here to help support and protect you.   800-428-9071

name: NY AG James
tweet: Billing sexual assault survivors for rape kits is illegal.   After we discovered that hospitals in NY were wrongfully billing survivors for these tests, we took legal action to hold them accountable & ensure these survivors were taken care of.    https://t.co/CR8RMUeDjw

name: NY AG James
